To maximise the number
In a loop..
check for the first digit if it is equal to 9 then do nothing... go for the next digit of vector again check if it is equal 9 or not...if it is not equal to 9 then store the current digit in some 'temp' named variable
**Here temp = 1;**
and 'break'..then in the next loop replace all the digit with 9 if the digit is equal to variable 'temp' i.e all 1 will be replaced with 9


Reason we are checking with 9 is because if first digit is 9 then there is no need to do anything go for the next non 9 digit
 like 99881 will be be 99991(maximum)

**To minimise** simply hold the starting digit in temp2 variable and replace wherver it is found in the vector

