# Intuition
The initial intuition while approaching this problem can be to consider digits fulfilling the criteria either:
1. Digit with max occurences in the number.
2. Digit with highest place value.
3. Smallest digit in a number.

But on evaluation, you will find that the place value factor overpowers the other two criterias.

# Approach
Max: To get the max number possible, select the highest place value digit which is not 9 and replace all possible occurences of that digit with 9.

Min: Select the highest place value digit (num[0]) [even if this digit is 9] and replace all occurences of this number with 0.

Get the difference of the max-min: Voila!

# Complexity
# - Time complexity: O(log(num))

1. Converting the input number to a string using to_string(num) takes O(log(num)) time, where log denotes the logarithm with base 10.
2. The first while loop iterates through the string until it finds the first digit that is not equal to 9. In the worst case, all digits could be 9, so this loop can iterate up to O(log(num)) times.
3. The second while loop iterates through the string once and performs constant time operations inside the loop. Therefore, it also takes O(log(num)) time.

* Overall, the time complexity of the code is O(log(num))

# **- Space complexity: O(log(num))**
1. The string s is used to store the string representation of the input number. Its length is equal to the number of digits in the input number, which is O(log(num)).
2. The remaining variables (n, i, m, max, min, copy, and digit) are all single integers or constants, so they require constant space.

* Therefore, the space complexity of the code is O(log(num)).

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minMaxDifference(int num) {
        string s;
        int n=0;
        int i=0;
        s=to_string(num);
        int m=s[0]-'0';
        // cout<<"M:"<<m<<endl;
        while(i<s.size()){
            if(s[i]!='9'){
                n=s[i]-'0';
                break;
            }
            i++;
        }
        i=0;
        int max=0;
        int min=0;
        int copy=0;
        int digit=0;
        while(i<s.size()){
            digit=s[i]-'0';
            if(digit==n){
                digit=9;
            }
            max=max*10+digit;
            i++;
        }
        i=0;
        while(i<s.size()){
            digit=s[i]-'0';
            if(digit==m){
                digit=0;
            }
            min=min*10+digit;
            i++;
        }
        // cout<<max<<endl;
        // cout<<min<<endl;
        return max-min;
    }
};
```

