# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
#### To get max value:
- We try to the find the first digit in num whose value is not equal to 9. Then we replace that digit with 0 for all its occurances in num.
- In case we can't find this digit then we don't need to modify num, we can say max = num. Now max = modified number.
#### To get min value:
- Similarly we try to the find the first digit in num whose value is not equal to 0. Then we replace that digit with 9 for all its occurances in num. Now min = modified number.
- In case we can't find this digit then we don't need to modify num, we can say min = num.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
#### minMaxDifference method:
- x = first occurring digit that is not equal to 9. In case all digits in num are 9 then x = 9, since 9 will be returned from the find() method.
- y = first occurring digit that is not equal to 0. In case all digits in num are 0 then x = 0, since 0 will be returned by the find() method.
- If x equals 9 then max = num, else max = modified number where x is replaced with 9.
- If y equals 0 then min = num, else min = modified number where y is replaced with 0.
- Return max - min.

#### find method:
- By default initialize val to be the last digit in num, i.e. val = num % 10
- Change num = num / 10 (so that we can start considering from the last second digit onwards until the first digit)
- While num > 0, if digit d != n then val = d (note: n is either 0 or 9, based on the param value we have passed)
- Return val

#### modify method:
- modified number is initialized to 0
- Iterate through the digits of num from right to left.
- Digit d = n % 10, if d == find, then multiply replace with the multiplier else multiply d with the multiplier.
- Note the multiplier will be as follows: 1, 10, 100, 1000, 10000 and so on. We use this so that we can place our next digit in front of the current digits in the modified number.
- Consider e.g. 3456 where find = 3, replace = 9. Then the modified number will be as follows: 6, 56, 456, 9456.
    - 6*1    + 0
    - 5*10   + 6
    - 4*100  + 56
    - 9*1000 + 456

# Complexity
- Time complexity: **O(N)**
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: **O(1)**
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int modify(int num, int find, int replace){
        int modified = 0, n = 0, multiplier, d;
        while(num > 0){
            d = num % 10;
            multiplier = (int)Math.pow(10,n);
            modified += (d == find) ? replace*multiplier : d*multiplier;
            n++;
            num /= 10;
        }
        return modified;
    }
    public int find(int num, int n){
        int d, val = num%10;
        num /= 10;

        while(num>0){
            d = num%10;
            if(d != n) val = d;
            num /= 10;
        }
        return val;
    }
    public int minMaxDifference(int num) {
        int x, y, max, min;
        x = find(num, 9);
        y = find(num, 0);

        max = (x == 9) ? num : modify(num, x, 9);
        min = (y == 0) ? num : modify(num, y, 0);

        return  max - min;
    }
}
```

